title: Ten Must Have Essential Jazz Albums [-emidius-]
description:
The included are considered by many to be the top ten essential jazz albums of all time. Regardless of any jazz album ranking...they are truly MUST OWN albums without a doubt, with the number one album 'MILES DAVIS - KIND OF BLUE' actually being the number one selling jazz album of all time. I hope you enjoy this collection and I will be releasing further collections in the near future with the next being the 'Ten Essential Blues Albums' collection.

10. CHET BAKER - CHET

9. JOE HENDERSON - PAGE ONE

8. PHAROAH SANDERS - THEMBI

7. ORNETTE COLEMAN - THE SHAPE OF JAZZ TO COME

6. CANNONBALL ADDERLEY - SOMETHIN' ELSE

5. BILL EVANS - SUNDAY AT THE VILLAGE VANGUARD

4. SONNY ROLLINS - THE BRIDGE

3. THELONIOUS MONK - MISTERIOSO

2. JOHN COLTRANE - CRESCENT

1. MILES DAVIS - KIND OF BLUE
